name: Quincy Jones
summary: Music legend Quincy Jones, renowned for his collaborations with iconic artists such as Frank Sinatra, Michael Jackson, and many others, has passed away at the age of 91. Forbes hailed Jones' legacy as a testament to leadership, collaboration, and effortless cool. The New York Times celebrated Jones as a giant of American music, while the Los Angeles Times highlighted his pivotal role in shaping Michael Jackson's solo career. NPR explored the life of this singular artist, and Variety featured tributes from prominent figures such as Will Smith, Steven Spielberg, and LL Cool J, acknowledging his immeasurable impact on music. Rolling Stone listed 20 of Jones' most significant productions, including "Thriller" and "We Are the World." The Seattle Times examined Jones' connection to the city, and CNN showcased his life in pictures. Pitchfork also announced Jones' passing, acknowledging his profound contributions to the music industry.
